The paper deals with the modelling of societies of goal-directed agents and their regulation through negotiation and strategic games. This falls under the domain of game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), specifically multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the use of taxation mechanisms, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and social influence (cs.SI).
